      I made an appointment here after finding these reviews on Yelp, so it only feels fair to leave one confirming that all the five-stars are accurate! I had an urgent wisdom tooth situation and got a last minute appointment with Dr. Tran after a bad / rude consultation elsewhere in the city.

      Dr. Tran was immediately friendly, patient and transparent; she answered my questions about the process thoroughly and made sure I had a pain-management prescription and aftercare instructions all in hand BEFORE she actually pulled the tooth.

      The extraction itself was quick and painless. She did an expert job (and managed my extreme anxiety gracefully); I'm now day 3 post-op and haven't even experienced face or tooth soreness or bruising for a moment. It's like nothing happened. She's now my dentist for life!

    • Dorothy Y.
      Elite 24
      New York, NY
      33
      301
      748
      May 4, 2022
      Updated review

      I just has my biannual checkup again!
      First time seeing Dr. Ong but not much to comment since I only saw her for a few minutes. Polite and nice.

      Most of this review is for Angela the hygienist.

      New things to note
      Angela performed an oral and neck cancer screening which was touching the inside and outside of my mouth and sides of neck toake sure nothing feels weird. I'm going to assume this is another item covered by my insurance during biannual checkups but regardless I appreciate the service.
      I was also told in the beginning that my insurance covers flouride treatment too, so I got that at the end. It was a sticky white paste. Angela told me I can eat and drink after thirty minute. I'm glad I didn't and kept my mask on until I got home. I couldn't rinse out the sticky white stuff from my teeth - had to brush it out.
      Another thing to note is the orange goggles they provide. It's actually useful in blocking out the treatment light - way better than my own glasses. It was a better idea for me to wear that than my own glasses, unless you're skirmish about germs - I'm sure they're happy to sanitize it for you if you mind.

      They took new x-rays since the previous ones were more than a year old.

      I appreciate how Angela gave me a detailed status of my teeth (e.g. a chipped tooth and how my old fillings are) rather than just saying everything's fine and call it a day.

      Similar to last time, she would place a guaze pad inside your cheek before placing the suction tube. She notices when you have too much saliva or buildup of water. She pauses to let you close your mouth to let the suction tube capture the extra fluids.
      Of course there would be splatters and drooling. Angela noticed and helped wipe too.
      Forgot if it happened last time but Angela gave me some vaseline when she noticed my lips were dry in the beginning.

      Most important of all, I came out with an obviously brighter smile and no discomfort. Appreciate Angela's attentiveness and thoughtfulness and patience during the whole treatment.

      Oct 20, 2021Previous review

      I went in for biannual checkup and cleaning.
      When I booked, I noticed their website had a different dentist. Upon arrival, I think everyone is new from the dentist to hygienist to reception! I wonder what happened to the old crew. Literally everything is the same except the people.

      I only saw Dr. Tran for like five minutes while she checked for cavities. Besides that not much interaction so not much I can comment on.

      Inside the appointment area, they didn't rent the air suction machine like they had back in April. The suction opening is as wide as my palm and they would put it over your mouth as you open up for them to do things. It felt nice to have but I'm ok they don't have it now. They offer goggles for patients now instead.

      Hygienist Angela. She's just as good as the previous Helen if not better. I had a lot of stains and plaque buildup so she spent a lot of time getting at them. Our appointment ran over the original allocated time by ~20min. It got to the point where I was thinking in my mind, wow she's still getting at it. I like how she added a gauze before hanging the suction tube in my mouth because that can soften the pushing and tugging on the insides of the mouth. When there was too much saliva or water in my mouth, she'd pause and tell me to close my mouth to let the suction tube get all the excess liquid before proceeding.
      I also asked if she can help clean my retainer because I had trouble getting at the buildup in the nooks and crannies. She was patient in answering any other questions I had about my teeth.
      She also escorted me out.

      Apr 16, 2021Previous review

      4.75* above and beyond, almost perfect

      I chose this clinic after looking on yelp. For some reason I thought there were multiple dentists but there's only one, Dr. Le.
      FYI their clinic is on the second floor. You have to walk up stairs to get there, no elevator.

      I arrived a little earlier than my appointment and was brought in a few minutes after my appointment time. There's a total of three dental seats.
      They have the end of the counter for me to put my stuff. It's wide and next to the computer.

      When I was seated the assistant asked me when was my last dental checkup, any problems with my teeth, and any specific reason I'm here today. The hygienist, Helen, and Dr. Le asked me the same questions when they saw me too.

      Then I was asked to rinse my mouth.

      The assistant took 6 x-rays as a follow up. I think this is the first dentist I've been to that does this at the biannual checkup.

      I saw Dr. Le first and she pointed out a chipped tooth. Not sure if it happened recently or other dentists never pointed out out but I appreciate she did. She also explained my specific tooth sensitivity is because of naturally deeper ridges. She did not recommend getting fillings for either, because the holes are too small and adding filling would require making the hole bigger. All three of these points were never mentioned by my previous dentists.
      As Dr. Le was scraping and poking around at each tooth she would mention things for the hygienist to make note of and pay attention to when cleaning my teeth.

      Hygienist Helen time.

      She checked the gum depth with this pointy thing. She did it to have a record and future reference. This is the first time I've ever had this measurement. I appreciate she let me have a swallow break every few teeth. The assistant would write down the measurement for each tooth.

      Forgot before or after gum depth measurement but Helen asked me if I cleaned under my bridge. I've never heard of a dentist mention that to me. She taught me how to carefully floss the gums underneath. It was a completely new phenomenon to me. Thanks so much for teaching this!!
      She was patient and let me ask all the questions I want.

      Then she started cleaning my teeth with the water gun thing. It did not hurt at all and no water seeped down my throat even without having an assistant chase the water gun during the procedure. My gums felt a little numb afterwards but doesn't bother me. One thing to complain was how water got on my face. I thought it was bad but my glasses proved it wasn't. Also everything dried out by the time she was done. They also had this vacuum machine thing above my head to suck up aerosol from my mouth during the cleaning. Instead of having a large light, the dentist and hygienist both had little head lights on their foreheads. I like how this is less bothersome to my eyes.
      Helen flossed my teeth after cleaning with the water gun. I've never had a dentist/hygienist floss me. I can't tell if this is good or bad but I appreciate it.
      Then she polished my teeth.

      Afterwards she gave me a mirror to check if everything is ok (thanks because I had to rinse more because there was polish between my teeth). Super glad and impressed the tartar was cleaned off my bridge. I thought it was a lost cause when previous dentist/hygienists didn't clean it much.
      Then Helen recapped the observations and discussions from today. I got the chance to ask more questions and she was glad to answer.
      Again I've never been to a dentist that would take the extra step doing all this.

      I got a goodie bag at the end with toothbrush, toothpaste, mouthwash, and dental floss.
      When I left I also saw how they wiped and sprayed everything in the area. Good good.

      Almost every step amazed me here. I left happy and look forward to going again.
